raw_data.title: Sr RF Systems Engineer
raw_data.description: Perform link budget calculations, determine the best solution, and supervise a field team in the integration of the cellular solution.  Expert in different RF analysis tools, cable types, impedances, terminations, and best use practices. Able to clearly and effectively communicate to the customer the process and expectations on the installation.  Researches, designs, writes edits and proofreads technical documents prior to publication. Coordinates and schedules installation teams and acts as a liaison between the installation teams and the customer when needed.  Coordinates, scheduling and production of all supporting technical material and manuals. Knowledge of word processing, page layout and design, graphics and ability to integrate into desktop publishing systems.

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: Planning and overseeing the activity and project management of information technology projects. Perform link budget calculations, determine the best solution, and supervise a field team in the integration of the cellular solution.  Coordinates with various computer hardware and network vendors to identify the best solution for the customer and organize the integration with their system.  Expert in different best use practices relating to hardware acquisition, software implementation, job site workflow, and testing. Able to clearly and effectively communicate to the customer the process and expectations on the installation and keep them informed throughout the process.  Researches, writes edits and proofreads technical documents prior to publication. Coordinates and schedules installation teams and acts as a liaison between the Chief Executive Officer, Senior RF Systems Engineer and the customer when needed.  Coordinates, scheduling and production of all supporting technical material and manuals. Knowledge of word processing, page layout and design, graphics and ability to integrate into desktop publishing systems.

raw_data.title: Sr RF Systems Supervisor
raw_data.description: Lead team in the preparation, deployment, and installation of cellular system. Follow/adjust link budget calculations, alter the solution when required, and supervise a field team in the integration of the cellular solution.  Expert in various RF analysis tools and equipment. Highly proficient in different cable types, terminations, and best use practices. Able to supervise and train technicians when needed.  Able to clearly and effectively communicate to the customer the process and expectations on the installation.  Follows and adjusts installation team’s timeline and acts as a liaison between the installation teams, the Senior RF Systems Engineer, and the customer when needed.  Knowledge of word processing, page layout and design, graphics and ability to integrate into desktop publishing systems

raw_data.title: RF Systems Technician
raw_data.description: Prepare, deploy, and install cellular systems and all associated equipment. Act as part of a team, and independent, when necessary, in the integration of the cellular solution.  Able to understand RF analysis tool readings and how to make necessary adjustments based on the results.  Apprentice in various RF analysis tools and equipment. Knowledgeable in different cable types, terminations, and best use practices. Able to assist and train other technicians when needed.  Able to communicate to the RF Team Leader and Senior RF Systems Engineer clearly and effectively when needed.  Able to professionally communicate at all times.  Knowledge of word processing, page layout and design, graphics and ability to integrate into desktop publishing systems.
raw_data.key_words: installation,part of a team,be independent,knowledge in cable,rf tools
